.TH "hid_hw_open" 9 "hid_hw_open" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
hid_hw_open \- signal underlying HW to start delivering events
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" hid_hw_open
.BI "(struct hid_device *hdev "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hdev" 12
hid device
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Tell underlying HW to start delivering events from the device.
This function should be called sometime after successful call
to \fBhid_hw_start\fP.
